# --- Type/Array GET: ToObjectFromJson<T>() doesn't support complex element types ---
# Typed convenience method returns use ToObjectFromJson<IReadOnlyList<T>>() which
# works for primitives (int, string, float, bool, DateTimeOffset) but fails for:
# - TimeSpan: ISO 8601 duration format not supported by default JSON serializer
# - Model: Internal parameterless constructor not accessible to JsonSerializer
# - BinaryData: Not JSON-serializable
# Fix: Use JsonDocument.Parse + element-level deserialization for these types.
DurationValueGet
ModelValueGet
NullableModelValueGet
UnknownValueGet

# --- Type/Dictionary PUT: BinaryContentHelper.FromObject() doesn't support Dictionary<string, T> ---
# Dict body params use BinaryContentHelper.FromObject(body) which calls WriteObjectValue<T>()
# that doesn't handle Dictionary<TKey, TValue>. Affects all dict PUT convenience methods.
# Fix: Use BinaryContent.Create(BinaryData.FromObjectAsJson(body)) or add dict support
# to WriteObjectValue.
BooleanPut
DatetimeValuePut
DurationValuePut
Float32ValuePut
Int32ValuePut
Int64ValuePut
ModelValuePut
NullableFloatValuePut
RecursiveModelValuePut
StringPut
UnknownValuePut

# --- Type/Dictionary GET: same complex type deserialization issue as Array GET ---
DurationValueGet
ModelValueGet
RecursiveModelValueGet
UnknownValueGet

# --- Payload/MediaType: text/plain serialization issue ---
# Convenience methods use BinaryContentHelper.FromObject() for text/plain body params,
# which JSON-serializes the string instead of sending raw text. Similarly,
# response deserialization uses ToObjectFromJson<string>() which fails on raw text.
# Fix: Detect text/plain content-type and use raw BinaryContent / text parsing.
GetAsText
SendAsText

